snippet.title: Is Notre Dame de Paris Worth It?
snippet.description:
Is Notre Dame de Paris worth it? I think that the cathedral of Notre Dame de Paris is amazing, personally. Link to the public LA Meetup poll below. Help me make better videos at http://patreon.com/jayswanson and then find me on the internet in all of the usual spots:
http://twitter.com/jayonaboat
http://instagram.com/jayswanson (me) http://bit.ly/ShirtOfTheMonth (merch)
http://bit.ly/JaySwansonBooks (my books)
http://bit.ly/CameraFour (Disposable Camera Four digital scans)

Music by: Dyalla
LA Meetup Date Poll: https://www.patreon.com/posts/19161141

The cathedral of Notre Dame de Paris is one of my absolute favorites. Is Notre Dame de Paris worth it? Absolutely. It's free, quick to get in, and really nice to wander through and even sit and contemplate life for a little bit. The cathedral of Notre Dame is one of the best examples of Gothic Architecture in the world - certainly in France - and it shows.

My name is Jay Swanson - I'm an American writer living in Paris on an artist visa and hoping to make the city of light my home base - at least for the foreseeable future. I write science-fiction and fantasy, vlog daily, and love pizza a little too much.

FAQ:
How long have you lived in France? On and off for over two years.

What do you miss most about ho- NACHOS

You're always talking about living on some ship. WHAT SHIP? - I made a "Draw My Life" video that explains a lot here: https://youtu.be/-MrvL37jTKM

Where are you from originally? - Pullman, Washington - a small university/agricultural town near Idaho (and yes, the potatoes are amazing).

What do you film with? - I currently film almost exclusively with my Samsung Galaxy S8: http://amzn.to/2lPKSpZ

How do you get those shots where you're walking or running? - A Joby Gorillapod for smartphones, like this: http://amzn.to/2sXNIL3

You drop your phone a lot, how does it survive? - THIS CASE IS AMAZING: http://amzn.to/2hoxgTA (Galaxy S7) - http://amzn.to/2Dt08Bu (Galaxy S8) - http://amzn.to/2FxVliP (iPhone)

What do you edit with? - Adobe Premiere - it's pretty much all I've ever used since high school.

Aren't you ever freaked out by leaving your camera behind to film yourself? - Yep. But not too badly - I tend to be careful when I do.

Why are you living in #Paris? - Because I've always wanted to; I feel at home here: https://youtu.be/4Vivf6MqMxQ

But what are you doing there? - Living it up! https://youtu.be/ZW2RP--DO8Y

Do you speak French? Oui. https://youtu.be/va1QjaHgij8

You talk a lot about the books you're working on, what are they about? - They're sci-fi (and fantasy) and I've got a decent pitch for you here: https://youtu.be/W2bKt4_Tp4E

Do you make money off YouTube? - Ha, no. I wish. It took me over 500 videos to make my first $100 off adsense. I think it will slowly change, but VERY slowly.

I really enjoy your videos, how can I support you? - The easiest and best way to support me is through Patreon, where you can pitch in as little as $1/mo to help me make better videos: http://patreon.com/jayswanson

I don't trust this Patreon thing - what's your PayPal? - Here's a handy link! https://www.paypal.me/jayswanson

I like PayPal in pink! - Here's my ko-fi if that's your thing (and coffee is your game): https://ko-fi.com/jayswanson

But I want to send you something tangible! - I do have a wishlist on Amazon, though it's a bit complicated with the international shipping situation. This is the US one: http://amzn.to/2ykS9Ux

And here's the French one: http://bit.ly/JaysFrenchWishList

Can I come stay with you in Paris? - Have you seen my apartment? It's too small for me as it is! https://youtu.be/6t2qj3rdyX8

OK, but how do I use the Metro when I'm there? - I made a handy video for you: https://youtu.be/T0YS5si8bJs

comments.textDisplay: I agree that Notre Dame is amazing, but so many European cathedrals are. For people visiting Paris it's worth wandering round the whole area around ND - it's where the city began.

That dog walker on the Segway was too funny.
The building of the cathedrals is pretty interesting, even with ones smaller than Notre Dame de Paris, it was often a communal effort often lasting multiple generations. I don't know if you read Ken Follett's "Pillars of the earth" but there's a hint of that in it.

comments.textDisplay:
I've been many times in this area. But only twice inside. My first visit to paris something like 20 years ago, and then the last visit 2 weeks ago.
If you are getting up early- I think it's the best time to see the inside, I don't know when it's open regularly but it was Pentecôte, so I was there around 07:00 o'clock, and there were very few people- almost nobody actually, I just got inside and could admire the place without suffocating from the crowd, which was lovely! In the afternoon there was also a ceremony, which was nice to watch as a spectacle.
I also think that people should see the place at night- beautifully lit :)

comments.textDisplay: We loved Notre Dame when we visited last week.  Such an awe inspiring place.  Those bleachers weren't there when we were...wonder what's going on.  Also, one fascinating thing about those gargoyles....one night when it was pouring rain, my wife noticed as she looked across from the apartment we stayed at, that the gargoyles are rain spouts.  Every single gargoyle had water pouring from it's mouth during the storm.  Now, off to catch up on a week's vlogging I missed out on while there.

comments.textDisplay:
Hey Jay, what day would you suggest is best for visiting Versailles? And which company for bike rental would you say is good, both Versailles and Paris wise?
I'm limited to Sun-Wed time frame.
comments.textOriginal:
Hey Jay, what day would you suggest is best for visiting Versailles? And which company for bike rental would you say is good, both Versailles and Paris wise?
I'm limited to Sun-Wed time frame.

replies.textDisplay: I definitely recommend Sunday or Tuesday with Bike About Tours (those are both outdoor market days - Tuesday is best because the French have to work so it's less crowded). You can sign up with them here http://bit.ly/BikeAboutToursJay and then mention me when you reserve if you don't mind (they'll hook you up with one of my stickers and I'll get a referral out of it 😀). They're the ones I worked with last year and their guides are great. I'm planning to go on a Versailles tour again here soon myself. The nice part about having a bike and a guide is that you get around more quickly, and with someone who helps to keep you from wasting time in the wrong spaces while helping you find things you would never on your own.
